That’s a bit weird, but do you have a RoboRIO 1? If so, you need to disable the NI webserver to free up some memory (as pathplannerlib requires numpy and numpy requires extra memory). You can disable it via robotpy installer niweb disable, just make sure that if you need to reimage your rio then you need to enable the webserver.

I don’t see how you came to the conclusions about the error’s source by just the information that you posted.

If you have a stack trace, or can isolate the error to individual lines of code or statements, that would be helpful. The error message you described above really shouldn’t be showing to a user as it’s not particularly useful.

If it is a purely pathplannerlib issue, you might try filing a big on their GitHub repo.
